Caribbean Sunset 510​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
My family and I took a trip to the western Caribbean over the Christmas holiday. I was able to soak up some tropical sun and swim in the warm water! I also took a lot of reference photos.  This little Polaroid painting is from one of the many amazing sunsets. More paintings to come!!!​​​​​​​​

Lighthouse at Punta Sur ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Another little Polaroid painting. This picturesque lighthouse is located in Cozumel, Mexico. I had no idea Cozumel was an island. Such a beautiful place!​​​​​​​​

Happy Groundhog Day! Here in the northern hemisphere we are right in the middle of winter and in Texas, the middle of a nasty ice storm. I noticed this beautiful winter photo going around Pinterest and decided to paint it.  I would love to credit the photographer, let me know if it was you. As far as winter, I hope the groundhog predicts an early spring and much warm weather. ​​​​​​​​

I love looking at all the abstract neurographic art paintings and decided to make my own version on a little bookmark in the spirit of Valentine’s. I think it’s a great way to try new colors palettes too. On a side note, these pens from @thepigeonletters are the best! Nice rounded tips, windows to see the tip, sizes on the pen and cap, they are archival and waterproof! Love, love, love them! If you like pens I definitely recommend!!!

Spring is finally here, the beginning of my favorite part of the year. The Texas bluebonnets and Indian paintbrush are just starting to bloom and everything is turning green again! I took the reference photo for this painting last spring and finally had a chance to paint it. This one is ready for my three day outdoor art show in April and prints are on order! Let me know what you think. ​​​​​​​​

New polaroid painting with a handmade driftwood stand! 

I have been a little quiet for a few months now on IG, but I am still painting. I love looking at all the art on IG, just frustrated with everything on this platform being pushed toward videos. As a full time teacher I just don’t have time to do all the work it takes to create videos, and I’d rather be painting. Also frustrated with IG because I am not seeing some of my favorite artists posts. I am not trying to complain, but this is more of why I have not been present. 

If you are still reading, I love the polaroid and driftwood combination. I am selling them on Etsy. Link in bio.

Red Poppy Triptych

There is just something about red poppies! I am super excited to complete this painting, it was started back in the summer. Now I am working to finish a few more paintings that have been abandoned since school started. I hope you have a fantastic week during this holiday season.

The Lone Poppy

This is my final poppy painting in a small series. Red poppies are definitely one of my favorite flowers to paint. I am trying to be better about framing my art once finished and I love how this turned out. I am not usually one for fancy frames, but I think it works for this painting. Let me know what you think!
